HEADWORD: calceolaria
<hw>cal`ce*o*la"ri*a</hw>
<pr>(k⟦acr⟧l`s⟦esl⟧*⟦osl⟧*l⟦amac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. L. <ets>calceolarius</ets> shoemaker, fr.
<ets>calceolus</ets>, a dim. of <ets>calceus</ets> shoe.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of showy herbaceous or shrubby plants,
brought from South America; slipperwort. It has a yellow or purple
flower, often spotted or striped, the shape of which suggests its
name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calceolate</ent>⟦br⟧
